	   <a name=96655290315146></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96655290315146><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>The Erudite SK</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 6:55 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am a mere 21st EruSK so make no preconceptions about how things will be at higher levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;I do however know how things are now.  As a Erudite we have passibly the worst stats for a melee class (but we look dam good in armor).  When I created I put all my points into STR.  This unfortunately left me with 70 AGI and 70 DEX.  Really you should never have a melee stat below 75.  I found this out the hard way.  It did however make my choice of equipment quite easy, as I focused on AGI/DEX with serp bracers ect.  <br>     Since I was a erudite I began with 117 INT.  After this patch that gave us the equivelent of a caster mana pool, I was extremely pleased.  This amount of mana allows me to heal myself a considerable amount, and save me much downtime.  As well it allows to to fear/kite relatively effeciently.  More on that later.  <br>     The first thing you should do as a EruSK is play around in the newbie gardens of Paineel and get to around level 5 or so (later if you arent familair with the sewers of Qeynos).  once you have reached an apprpriate level you will quickly find why Odus is the least populated continent.  Least for anyone below 35.  So you must venture fourth to make your legend know.  <br>     Taveling through Qeynos is a pain as we have to do it through the sewers.  Once you arrive try and get bound immediately.  Then under one of the docks is the underwater entrance to the sewers.  For a maps see <a href="http://www.eqatlas.com." target=_new>http://www.eqatlas.com.</a>  Work your way through the sewers to west Qeynos (or whatever its called) and get bound again (the sewer can be a rough trip, better to only do it once).  Now you have some options.  Being familair with the way I  simply made the run to Freeport to begin my career.  However, it could be safer and more advantageous to hang out in the hills and in Blackburrow for about 5 levels or so and make 10th.  You should be careful to con all NPCs in the hils as I remember several didn't much care for me.<br>     Once you have killed enough gnolls you can actually travel safely through Qeynos.  Though as I said I didnt stick around here much as I dont much care for the area.  I went directly to FP.  <br>     As for everything else you can pretty much follow any of the other guides that apply to any other Sk as far as where to fight ect.<br><br>Just my 2 cents.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
